# CodeMind AI — Day 0 & Day 1 Planning

## Day 0 — Pre-Hackathon Setup (2–3 Hours, Evening)
- [ ] Read & lock MVP scope (5 core features only)
- [ ] Set up GitHub repo & project folder structure (`/backend`, `/frontend`, `/agents`)
- [ ] Verify dev environment: Node.js, npm, VS Code, API keys
- [ ] Install dependencies & test OpenAI/Claude API connectivity
- [ ] Write product backlog & assign Day 1 tasks
- [ ] Create `.env` file with all required environment variables

## Day 1 — Project Setup & Core Foundation (9:00 AM – 5:00 PM)
- [ ] Morning kickoff: review Day 1 tasks together
- [ ] **Person A**: Backend scaffold — Express server on port 3000, `GET /health`
- [ ] **Person B**: Frontend scaffold — Next.js + Monaco Editor setup
- [ ] **Person A**: Install AI SDK (LangChain/OpenAI) + test API call
- [ ] **Person B**: Monaco Editor integration — syntax highlighting, basic layout
- [ ] Mid-morning sync: share progress + unblock
- [ ] **Person A**: Create API routes — `/api/v1/generate`, `/api/v1/autocomplete`
- [ ] **Person B**: Build editor UI zones (sidebar, toolbar, editor, terminal panel)
- [ ] **Person A**: Implement PromptBuilder class + system prompts
- [ ] **Person B**: Connect AI prompt panel to backend API
- [ ] Integration test: frontend → backend → AI → response displayed
- [ ] Fix bugs + Git commit Day 1 progress
